snippet.textDisplay: With 2 young kids at home full time now I focus my attention on helping with their studies. They constantly eat so I'm in the kitchen 3-4 hours a day and the rest of the time we're finding things to do like long walks around the streets and kicking a ball around the back yard. I've not trained in weeks and I kind of enjoy it not having to be sore all the time. I eat a lot less than I used to. Meals are a few eggs with spinach, onions and mushy's in the morning, couple black coffee's during the day, toasted cheese and tomato sandwich for lunch and some frozen veges with 1/2 cup rice/1-2 potatoes with vegan meatballs and/or mozzarella cheese/bbq sauce. I jumped on the scales the other day and I was a kilo heavier than the few weeks before. Just mucking around with the kids each day is making me stronger since my belly fat is slowly decreasing. Who needs the gym hey :D.
